<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_properties_of_a_polygon">How to Calculat=
e the Properties of a Polygon</h2>
<p>
A polygon is a two-dimensional shape made up of straight <a href=3D"https:/=
/www.inchcalculator.com/equation-of-a-line-calculator/">line segments</a>.
</p>
<p>
A regular polygon is a symmetrical polygon where all of the sides are equal=
 in length, and all angles have the same angle. Examples of regular polygon=
s include <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/equilateral-triangle-ca=
lculator/">equilateral triangles</a>, squares, <a href=3D"https://www.inchc=
alculator.com/pentagon-calculator/">pentagons</a>, <a href=3D"https://www.i=
nchcalculator.com/hexagon-calculator/">hexagons</a>, and <a href=3D"https:/=
/www.inchcalculator.com/octagon-calculator/">octagons</a>.
</p>
<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_area_of_a_polygon">How to Calculate the =
Area of a Polygon</h2>
<p>
The <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/area-calculator/">area</a> of=
 a polygon largely depends on its size and shape. You can calculate the are=
a using a formula. For a regular polygon with <em>n</em> sides of length <e=
m>a</em>, the formula to find the area is:</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1=
_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-content adthrive-content-1" style=
=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
<div class=3D"latex latex--mh6 latex--left latex--mode-display latex--bg-gr=
ey loaded" data-latex=3D"" data-latex-alignment=3D"left" data-latex-mode=3D=
"display"><span class=3D"katex-display fleqn"><span class=3D"katex"><span c=
lass=3D"katex-mathml"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" di=
splay=3D"block"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>=3D</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>=CF=
=80</mi><mo>=C3=97</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>4<=
/mn><mo>=C3=97</mo><mi>t</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">(</=
mo><mi>=CF=80</mi><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">/</mi><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=
=3D"false">)</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/=
x-tex">A =3D \frac{\pi \times a^{2}}{4 \times tan( \pi / n)}</annotation></=
semantics></math></span><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><sp=
an class=3D"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6833em;"></span>=
<span class=3D"mord mathnormal">A</span><span class=3D"mspace" style=3D"mar=
