<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_find_the_angles_of_a_polygon">How to Find the Angles o=
f a Polygon</h2>
<p>
The interior angles of a polygon are the angles formed inside the polygon w=
here two sides meet. Every polygon, whether regular or irregular, has inter=
ior angles that sum up to a certain value based on the number of sides it h=
as.
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_3_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-co=
ntent adthrive-content-3" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
<p>
For any polygon, the sum of its interior angles, taken one per vertex, alwa=
ys equals <span class=3D"formula formula-small">(n =E2=80=93 2) =C3=97 180=
=C2=B0</span>.
</p>
<p>
Therefore, the formula to calculate the interior angle <em>=CE=B1</em> of a=
 regular polygon is:
</p>
<div class=3D"latex latex--mh6 latex--left latex--mode-display latex--bg-gr=
ey loaded" data-latex=3D"" data-latex-alignment=3D"left" data-latex-mode=3D=
